The paper discusses the use of Bayesian optimization in improving the playing strength of AlphaGo, which is an AI system designed to play the board game Go. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the tuning of hyper-parameters, which is a common technique in machine learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques in AlphaGo, which could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the game theory aspects of Go, which could place it in the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category.
